@latimes But no one should be held in these conditions with no explanation while being denied due process. We must hold ICE and Donald Trump accountable and demand humane treatment for all in custody.
@latimes I advocated continuously for his release, and I’m grateful he is finally home with his wife, the chief of medical staff at Huntington Hospital in Pasadena.

When I toured this facility with my colleagues in Congress, ICE officials tried to assure us that conditions were good. But Rami’s firsthand account tells a different story: sleeping on concrete floors, little food, no medical care. Even Rami’s ICE caseworker didn’t understand why he was being held there.

I’m relieved my constituent Rami Othmane, a Tunisian green-card applicant battling a brain tumor, has finally been released, but we cannot ignore his wrongful detention and the inhumane conditions he experienced. This @latimes piece exposes the horrific conditions that Rami and so many others endure in ICE custody. This is not justice.

This is reckless and cruel. Slashing $350 million in Congressionally-approved funds from colleges serving minority, first-generation, and low-income students to fund handouts for the wealthy shows yet again exactly where this administration’s priorities lie. These cuts will destabilize colleges, gut support services for students, rob millions of their shot at the American Dream, and ultimately harm our nation's economic future.

Trump’s sabotage is slowing our economy and blocking investments in medical research, health care, infrastructure, schools, and more. Today marks 24 years since 9/11 —  a day we lost 2,977 innocent lives to a horrendous act of terrorism. As we remember those lost, I'm proud to cosponsor the 9/11 Responder and Survivor Health Funding Correction Act to ensure that all those still suffering from 9/11-related conditions have access to the care they need & deserve.

We will #NeverForget

This bill will expand access to life-saving eating disorder treatment for seniors.

Eating disorders affect seniors at rates similar to the general population, but Medicare doesn’t cover Medical Nutrition Therapy (MNT) for these conditions, leaving seniors & people with disabilities without access to necessary treatment.
